        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Gemini web search freshness handling",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nGemini-backed `web_search` could fail when callers passed relative `freshness` values like `day`. OpenClaw mapped those shortcuts to Gemini `google_search.timeRangeFilter`, but the Gemini endpoint rejects some relative hard ranges, including the same-day shape seen in production, before any grounded result is returned.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis keeps explicit `date_after` / `date_before` behavior as the hard Gemini Google Search grounding time range path, while changing relative `freshness` shortcuts to a query-level recency instruction. That preserves the user's intent to prioritize recent sources without sending an invalid hard filter to Gemini.\n\nThe cache key now includes the freshness shortcut even though the hard filter is omitted, so cached responses for the same query remain separated by recency intent.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers can keep calling Gemini `web_search` with `freshness: \"day\"`, `week`, `month`, or `year` without the request being rejected by Gemini's time range validation. When a hard grounding range is required, users can still use `date_after` and `date_before`.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/google/web-search-provider.test.ts` passed.\n- `pnpm test:extension google` passed: 26 test files, 349 tests.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/google/src/gemini-web-search-provider.ts extensions/google/src/gemini-web-search-provider.runtime.ts extensions/google/web-search-provider.test.ts` passed.\n- `node scripts/format-docs.mjs --check docs/tools/gemini-search.md docs/tools/web.md` passed.\n- `codex review --base origin/main` passed with no introduced actionable correctness issues after the schema/docs update.\n- Live operational validation before this PR: patched Gemini `web_search(freshness=day)` completed successfully on an OpenClaw gateway, with no Gemini `FIELD_INVALID` / `time_range_filter` errors in the post-deploy journal window.\n\nKnown gap: `pnpm build` was attempted on current `origin/main` and failed outside this changed surface because `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.ts` imports a missing `resolveEnforceFinalTagWithResolver` export from `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-run-params.ts`. This branch changes only the Gemini web search provider/docs/tests.\n\n## AI Assistance\n\nAI-assisted: yes. Prepared with Codex. I understand the changed code path: relative Gemini freshness no longer creates a hard `timeRangeFilter`; explicit date ranges still do; and cache partitioning keeps freshness-specific responses separate.\n",
